
            Video
            Dutch explorer drives tractor to the South Pole
            A Dutch explorer has driven to the South Pole in a tractor.Manon Ossevoort has made the journey in a Massey Ferguson, the company which provided equipment to Sir Edmund Hilary for his expedition to Antarctica in 1958.Speaking to the BBC, she said she had achieved "an impossible dream".
                
                        09 Dec 2014
                    
                
        
